      {"q": "Intermittent faults appearing simultaneously across multiple avionics LRUs sharing the same data bus most likely points to:", "choices": ["A coincidental failure of all units at once", "A shared bus wiring/termination problem rather than multiple independent unit failures", "Normal operation", "A software update requirement only"], "answer": 1, "explain": "Simultaneous intermittent faults across multiple units sharing a bus is a strong indicator of a shared bus wiring or termination issue, not independent coincidental failures."},
